
{center}
{subhead} fxPAINT Released!{def}
{left}
{p} {p}

PRESSRELEASE,  7.11.1999{p}
FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE
{p} {p}
Innovative, the developers of successful AMIGA-products like fxSCAN or VLRec NG today
announced the availability of fxPAINT. fxPAINT is a new imageprocessing- and paintingprogram
with a gigantic functionality, an intuitive userinterface and support for the latest standards
and hardware. Furthermore fxPAINT is the first application to fully support the new features of
OS 3.5.
{p} {p}
The features:
{p} {p}
         · Support of existing hardware{p}
                ·  Scanner (using RBM`s ScanQuix){p}
                ·  VHI-grabber (for VLab (not Motion) and other videoboards){p}
                ·  graphic tableaus
{p} {p}
         · Creation of new pictures and textures as basic function{p}
                ·  Fractals{p}
                ·  Fire{p}
                ·  Screengrabber
{p} {p}
         · Full PPC-Support{p}
                ·  PPC-support was included from the beginning on{p}
                ·  Support of WarpUP and PowerUP (ppc.lib){p}
                ·  Open PPC-support allows support for theoretically every (maybe new) PPC-Driver-System
{p} {p}
         · Optimized printing routines{p}
                ·  Support for TurboPrint{p}
                ·  Support for old printer.device{p}
                ·  Support for the new API in AmigaOS 3.5
{p} {p}
         · 24 Bit-Alpha-Channel{p}
                ·  Easy usage and choosing{p}
                ·  Full control over transparency effects{p}
                ·  aimed changing of red-, green- and blue-compentents of an image
{p} {p}
         · Open and publically documented Plugin-API fxPLUGIN for{p}
                ·  Loader-Modules{p}
                ·  Saver-Modules{p}
                ·  Effect-Modules{p}
                ·  Displaydrivers{p}
                ·  Modules for additional functionality
{p} {p}
         · Over 70 effects and special effects{p}
                ·  Effects are being calculated and displayed in realtime{p}
                ·  Effects are sorted by categories (-> find wanted effect fast){p}
                ·  Anti "red eyes"{p}
                ·  Antique{p}
                ·  Black&White{p}
                ·  Bluebox{p}
                ·  Bumpmapper (3D-Logos with shadows, glow, etc){p}
                ·  Buttonborder{p}
                ·  Clone{p}
                ·  Colourize{p}
                ·  Compose{p}
                ·  Convolution{p}
                ·  Correction (Brightness, Gamma, R, G, B){p}
                ·  Create border{p}
                ·  Create wave{p}
                ·  Deinterlace{p}
                ·  Draw{p}
                ·  Dithering (14 different methods){p}
                ·  Distortion (Radial and quadratic){p}
                ·  Earthquake{p}
                ·  Embed/Watermark Plugin (using PHILTH){p}
                ·  Emboss{p}
                ·  Explosion-Tile{p}
                ·  Fisheye{p}
                ·  Gaussian blur{p}
                ·  Gradation-curve{p}
                ·  Glow{p}
                ·  Oil-Painting{p}
                ·  Pagecurl{p}
                ·  Pixelise{p}
                ·  Posterize{p}
                ·  Pyro functions{p}
                ·  RGB-Shifting{p}
                ·  Remove isolated pixels{p}
                ·  Replace color{p}
                ·  RLE compression optimizer{p}
                ·  Rotate{p}
                ·  Rubthrough{p}
                ·  Scale{p}
                ·  Selective Gaussian Blur{p}
                ·  Shear{p}
                ·  Silhouette{p}
                ·  Smooth{p}
                ·  Spread{p}
                ·  Straw{p}
                ·  Supernova{p}
                ·  Texture{p}
                ·  Tile{p}
                ·  TV Lace{p}
                ·  ICS Color Correction{p}
                ·  Insert brush{p}
                ·  Invert/Negative{p}
                ·  Lightsource{p}
                ·  Lightspeed{p}
                ·  Limit RGB{p}
                ·  Logic{p}
                ·  Maximum{p}
                ·  Median{p}
                ·  Minimum{p}
                ·  MinMax{p}
                ·  Mirage{p}
                ·  Mirror{p}
                ·  Mosaic (replace a picture with smaller ones){p}
                ·  Motion (Blur){p}
                ·  Move{p}
                ·  Noise{p}
                ·  Waves{p}
                ·  Zoom-Blur{p}
                ·  etc.
{p} {p}
         · Extended painting tools{p}
                ·  Magic Stick (Pantograph)-function{p}
                ·  Gradients as basic tool{p}
                ·  Smear- and Blur-Tool{p}
                ·  usual basic-tools{p}
                ·  draw with fire
{p} {p}
         · integrated picture management with fxALBUM{p}
                ·  Fast catalogisation of pictures on your HD{p}
                ·  directly linked with fxPAINT and therefore has optimal abilities for image manipulation{p}
                ·  Printing of overviews{p}
                ·  Organisation as catalogues{p}
                ·  export as HTML-overviews
{p} {p}
         · integrated mini-converter fxCONV{p}
                ·  conversion of several dirs full of pictures with some clicks{p}
                ·  conversion from any to any format supported by fxPAINT
{p} {p}
         · Completly new library of loader- and saver-modules{p}
                ·  highly optimized{p}
                ·  read/write formats like ILBM, PCX, BMP, TARGA, JPEG, YUVN, LJPG, PNM, RGB8, TIFF, IFF24, ..{p}
                ·  preview of the JPEG-fractures
{p} {p}
         · own GUI-System{p}
                ·  Realisation as BOOPSI-Objects{p}
                ·  24Bit GUI-elements and gradients{p}
                ·  GUI contains many pictures{p}
                ·  Bubble-Help for easy usage{p}
                ·  three user-settable knownledge-degrees{p}
                ·  automatic fixation of window-positions{p}
                ·  GlowIcon-style{p}
                ·  no hacks, patches, etc.
{p} {p}
         · ARexx-support{p}
                ·  connect fxPAINT with all your favourite programs!
{p} {p}
         · AmigaOS 3.5 system enhancement{p}
                ·  systemconform{p}
                ·  allows fast overview of all your graphics{p}
                ·  direct linking of Workbench and fxALBUM, fxCONV and fxCONV
{p} {p}
         · Full AmigaOS 3.5 support{p}
                ·  OS 3.5 icons{p}
                ·  OS 3.5 printer support{p}
                ·  OS 3.5 workbench support{p}
                ·  OS 3.5 datatype support
{p} {p}
         · Internal modules{p}
                ·  fxALBUM{p}
                ·  fxCONV{p}
                ·  fxIMAGEMAP{p}
                ·  fxPLUGINs
{p} {p}
The price for fxPAINT is 77 US$/71 EURO. fxPAINT is available now.
